# Code Example

```python
def process_data(items):
    return [item * 2 for item in items]
Algorithmic Complexity

For an algorithm processing input size \(n\):

T(n) = n^2 + 3n + 2 = O(n^2) \\] Another example: \\[ f(n) = \log(n) + n\log(n) \\] --- # Custom Styled Block <div class="custom-box"> This is a custom-styled box using Marp CSS. Useful for alerts, warnings, or highlights. </div> --- # Conclusion - Fully version-controlled documentation - Convertible to HTML/PDF/PPTX - Customizable themes - Great for software product documentation **Contact:** 23f2004606@ds.study.iitm.ac.in ``` --- # ✅ **Where to host this** Create a GitHub repo: ``` my-marp-docs ``` Add `slides.md` (the file above). You can then convert using: ``` marp slides.md --pdf marp slides.md --html marp slides.md --pptx ``` --- # ❓ What is the Raw GitHub URL? Once uploaded, the raw URL will be: ``` https://raw.githubusercontent.com/[USER]/[REPO]/main/slides.md ``` For example, if your username is `rahul-dev` and repo is `my-marp-docs`: ``` https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rahul-dev/my-marp-docs/main/slides.md ``` --- If you want, I can: ✅ Generate a GitHub Actions workflow to automatically export PDFs ✅ Build a full folder structure with themes, assets, and CI ✅ Add a separate theme CSS file instead of inline styles Just say **“set up GitHub Actions”** or **“make repo structure”**.

